video.description:
SpaceX teams are conducting the first stacking operation of a Starship (Ship 20) onto a Super Heavy booster (Booster 4) in Starbase, Texas. The fullstack is being assembled ahead of Elon's Starship update on Thursday evening.

24x7 Coverage: http://www.nasaspaceflight.com/starbaselive

video.description:
Starship is SpaceX's fully reusable launch system which is being developed at Starbase in Cameron County, Texas. Starbase LIVE provides 24/7 coverage of the exciting developments and testing progress.

Get cool merch and support the stream: https://shop.nasaspaceflight.com/

video.title: Starbase LIVE: 24/7 Starship & Super Heavy Development From SpaceX's Boca Chica Facility

video.description:
02/08/2022 - Epic times! Starbase is a massive beehive of activity. SpaceX is moving quickly ahead of the Starship presentation on Thursday. S20 rolls into place via SPMTs for the first ever catch arm lift. Locking pin arms are also moved into place and aligned for deployment. You will notice the one missing tile. This is spot where the locking pin will insert.
